Globally, levonorgestrel is the most commonly used emergency contraceptive. It was initially granted FDA approval in 1982 and was the first emergency contraceptive containing only progesterone, showing high levels of efficacy and a lack of estrogenic adverse effects when compared to older emergency contraceptive regimens.[A181976,A181994,L7760]', '["G03AB03", "G03AD01", "G03AC03", "G03FB09", "G03AA07", "G03FA11"]', '[]');
